article.headline: Utah St. 88, CS Bakersfield 66
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. (AP) -- Jaycee Carroll poured in 27 points, including six 3-pointers, to lead Utah State to an 88-66 win Saturday over Cal State Bakersfield. Gary Wilkinson had 21 points, 17 in the first half, and Tai Wesley chipped in 12 for the Aggies (6-5). Terrence Johns finished with 20 points for Bakersfield (1-7), while Alex Johnson added 14 points, Zack Grasmick had 11 and Demarcus Hall 10 off the bench. Both teams shot better than 60 percent from beyond the 3-point arc in the first half, combining for 13 triples over that 20 minutes. But while Utah State stayed hot in the second half, hitting 60 percent from the field and beyond the arc, the Roadrunners went cold, making just six of 28 attempts. The Aggies stretched a 47-40 halftime lead to a 15-point advantage at the 15:26 mark on a jumper by Stephen DuCharme. While the Roadrunners would cut the lead to nine on two occasions midway through the half, Utah State responded both times.
